  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2865994243" />
    <a title="Kelie Killu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42251069-kelie-killu"><img alt="Kelie Killu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570155074p2/42251069.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2865994243?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelie Killu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelie Killu" href="/user/show/42251069-kelie-killu">Kelie Killu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2865994243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5537696205801328547">I had the pleasure of not only reading this amazing book but having it read to me by the author! This heartfelt book had me laughing and then crying so often that I couldn’t keep track of what actual emotion I was feeling!! I’m going to be honest and tell you that Richard is a dear friend of mine, but when I went to the reading, I knew very little about him (our friendship was somewhat new). I left with a whole knew respect for him and the things he had gone through in life. I remember telling s</span>
  <span id="freeText5537696205801328547" style="display:none">I had the pleasure of not only reading this amazing book but having it read to me by the author! This heartfelt book had me laughing and then crying so often that I couldn’t keep track of what actual emotion I was feeling!! I’m going to be honest and tell you that Richard is a dear friend of mine, but when I went to the reading, I knew very little about him (our friendship was somewhat new). I left with a whole knew respect for him and the things he had gone through in life. I remember telling shortly after that I too was a survivor of abuse. Something that I had not shared with those outside of my very small circle. <br /><br />During the reading, I looked around the room and realized that I was the only person there from work (that’s how I met Richard, through work). His book was so raw and so real that I instantly gained so much more respect for him than I already had (which was a ton). He inspired me to open up about my own experience with abuse and to join him on his Tenderness Tour as a volunteer. Thank you Richard for pouring your heart out and keeping it real with us all!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5537696205801328547" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


